Arsenal

Arsenal striker Olivier Giroud begins a three-match suspension so misses Sunday's Barclays Premier League trip to West Ham.

Olivier Giroud was sent off on Boxing Day after headbutting Nedum Onuoha

Giroud was sent off for head-butting in the 2-1 victory over QPR and sits out the Upton Park showdown, but Laurent Koscielny could be back from a hamstring problem.

Aaron Ramsey (hamstring), Mikel Arteta (calf), Mesut Ozil (knee), Abou Diaby (calf), Jack Wilshere (ankle) and Serge Gnabry (knee) are sidelined.

